🧭 The Rule Set (your “Modern Repass” for early Pokémon style)

1) Silhouette First
	•	One clean, readable shape
	•	Recognizable at a glance (even in black)

If you blur it, you should still know what it is.

⸻

2) One Core Idea
	•	Animal + element (fox + fire, fish + water, etc.)
	•	No stacking 3–4 concepts

Early mons = one strong hook, not a collage

⸻

3) Limited Detail Budget
	•	Few lines, intentional shapes
	•	Avoid over-texturing / over-patterning

Design should be drawable from memory

⸻

4) Color Discipline
	•	1–2 dominant colors + 1 accent
	•	No rainbow palettes or heavy gradients

⸻

5) Personality Through Shape
	•	Sharp = aggressive (Jolteon)
	•	Soft = calm (Vaporeon)
	•	Fluffy = warm (Flareon)

No need for lore to explain personality—the shape does it

⸻

6) Grounded Creature Logic
	•	Feels like it could exist (even if stylized)
	•	Not too humanoid, not too abstract

⸻

